God hath made of one blood all nations of men to dwell on the earth, in unity and blessedness. God has also bestowed certain rights alike on all men and all chiefs, and all people of all lands. These are some of the rights which He has given alike to every man and every chief of correct deportment; life, limb, liberty, freedom from oppression; the earnings of his hands and the productions of his mind, not however to those who act in violation of the laws.” \nKing Kamehameha III has issued a declaration of the rights inherent to the citizens of Hawai’i. Inspired by the republicanism and constitutional monarchies of the western powers, old traditions of absolute rule have begun to fade.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
KILAUEAGOESBOOM;“The hideous immensity itself, independent of the many frightful images which it embraced, almost caused an involuntary closing of the eyes against it. But when to the sight is added the appalling effect of the various unnatural and fearful noises, the muttering and sighing, the groaning and blowing, the every agonized struggling, of the mighty action within, as a whole, it is too horrible. And for the first moment I felt like one of my friends, who, on reaching the brink, recoiled, and covered his face, exclaiming, ‘Call it weakness, or what you please, but I cannot look again.’” - Stewart’s Journal of a Residence in the Sandwich Islands \nA great eruption of the volcano Kilauea has occurred, sending ash into the sky for twenty six days and nights, and reportedly allowing newspapers to be read by night as far away as Hilo.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
hawaiian_constitution_1840_title;Write the 1840 Constitution;;;;;;;;;;;;;
hawaiian_constitution_1840_desc;As our nation begins to modernize, our king has decided that it is high time to adopt a formal written constitution of our laws and government. It shall be written in a manner that allows for the common people to have some choice in government, while still giving the majority of the power to the king.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
HAWAIIANDOLAR;Until now, our population has mostly relied on traditional means of exchange or foreign currency for economic activity. However, the Kingdom has recently issued a number of coins bearing the face of our king, representing the new “Hawaiian Dollar.”;;;;;;;;;;;;;
MEASLESNOO;Although colonial diseases have been endemic ever since our first contact with the Europeans, an outbreak of measles has spread throughout the islands at an alarming rate, killing mainly native Hawaiians. The devastation has brought rural life to its knees, and allowed for plantations to acquire more land from dead and dying villages. \nIn time, the pandemic may clear, but for now measles rules Hawai’i.;;;;;;;;;;;;;
