LATTERSAINTSHAWAII;A strange religious movement has spread to Hawai’i. Missionaries from the Church of Latter Day Saints, colloquially known as “Mormons,” have settled in our kingdom. Although Christian, they have faced great persecution for their divergent beliefs from the rest of Protestant Christianity. Despite this, they have received some accolades for their actions.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
great_mahele_title;Begin the Great Mahele;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
great_mahele_desc;The old land management system of ancient times has grown inadequate for our modernizing nation. The arrival of plantations, mills, and industry has clashed with our past system of communal land ownership. We will privatize much of this land, and allow it to be sold to private and foreign interests in order to develop our kingdom.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CHINESEMIGRATION;With war and strife taking hold of China, many laborers have come to Hawai’i to seek refuge and employment. Plantation owners and industrialists will no doubt make use of their labor, especially as the native population declines from decades of disease.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
hawaiian_constitution_1852_title;The 1852 Constitution;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
hawaiian_constitution_1852_desc;Although the 1840 Constitution made great strides to the modernization of our kingdom, we still lag behind the governments of the western powers. Inspired by British and American administration, we shall reform into a proper constitutional monarchy and guarantee suffrage to all.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
KAMEHAMEHATHIRDDIES;Today is a tragic day for our kingdom. The King of the Hawaiian Islands, Kamehameha III, has suddenly passed at the age of forty. Seen as the great modernizer of the Kingdom, many will mourn his passing. His young adopted son and nephew shall rule as King Kamehameha IV.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
construct_haw_medical_title;Build the Queen’s Medical Center;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
construct_haw_medical_desc;Disease has ravaged our kingdom for decades and killed perhaps half of the native population of our islands. Our king, following a proposal from an American physician, has declared the construction of a grand hospital in our capital in order to halt the spread of disease.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
honolulu_rifles_title;Found the Honolulu Rifles;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
honolulu_rifles_desc;In order to protect and maintain internal order in our kingdom, the King has declared the foundation of a new military unit, comprised of Western soldiers, officers, and equipment. These “Honolulu Rifles” shall be the elite troops of our proud army.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
EOLAKEALIIKEAKUA;“Ke Akua Mana Mau, Ho'omaika'i, pomaika'i, I ka mo'i .” \nSince the time of Kamehameha I, our kingdom has traditionally used the British “God Save the King” as our royal anthem. However, the English anthem has sparked some concerns over the abandonment of our native tongue. In recognition of this, Prince Lunalilo has penned a translation of the tune into the native Hawaiian tongue to be used in its place.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
CHURCHOFHAWAII;Inspired by the United Kingdom’s Church of England, a proposal has reached us about the foundation of a state-backed “Church of Hawaii” in the Anglican tradition. Although this will surely anger the followers of other Protestant branches, it will greatly please the British investors and missionaries in our realm.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
annex_palmyra_atoll_title;Annex Palmyra Atoll;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
annex_palmyra_atoll_desc;The tiny atoll of Palmyra lies far to the south of our islands. Although not of significant strategic value, sending a contingent to annex it would prevent other powers from encroaching on our territorial waters.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
annex_midway_atoll_title;Annex Midway;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
annex_midway_atoll_desc;The chain of the Hawaiian Islands expands westward across a number of tiny atolls. Chief among these is Kauihelani, or “Midway, a small atoll which may see some use as a fishing outpost or coaling station. We must annex these tiny islands to expand our kingdom.
